                    <h3>Wrapper element</h3>
                    <p>The use of a wrapper element in web design includes:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Padding: Provides white space within the element</li>
                        <li>Centers the content: Helps keep the content centered for better readability and aesthetics
                        </li>
                        <li>Max-width: Sets a maximum width for the content</li>
                    </ul>

                    <p>
                        The old way to place a wrapper is:
                    </p>
                    <pre>
    <code>
    .wrapper {
        max-width: 75rem;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 0 1.5rem:
    }
    </code>
</pre>
                    <p>
                        This is a better way to place a wrapper:
                    </p>
                    <pre>
    <code>
    .wrapper {
        width: min(100% - 3em, 75rem);
        margin-inline: auto;
    }

    </code>
</pre>
